## Limitations

This report primarily focuses on the positive aspects of social media for teens, which may not provide a balanced view of the potential negative impacts, such as cyberbullying and mental health issues. Additionally, the findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all recent developments in social media trends. Further research is needed to explore the long-term effects of social media on teenagers' mental health and social development.